In this article, President Barack Obama declares November 2013 as Critical Infrastructure Security and Resilience Month. He emphasizes the importance of protecting the nation's critical infrastructure, which includes both physical and cyber systems. The President mentions that he has made protecting critical infrastructure a top priority and has signed a Presidential Policy Directive and Executive Order on cybersecurity to strengthen defenses against threats. He also emphasizes the need for information sharing and collaboration between the government, businesses, and industry leaders to enhance the security and resilience of critical infrastructure. The President calls on the people of the United States to recognize the importance of protecting the nation's resources and to observe the month with appropriate events and training to enhance national security and resilience.